description.plain:
Rolando Gomez (b. June 23, 1998), better known by his stage name Icy Narco, is an American recording artist coming straight out of Miami, Florida.

He first rose to fame following the release of “Viagra Niagra,” but later came into more mainstream spotlight under the wing of Elliot Grainge’s 10K Projects label, where he released songs such as “Numb & Frozen,” “Otherside,” and his biggest song to date, “LINK,” The success of these songs has helped him get onto major Hip-Hop media outlets such as XXL and WorldStarHipHop.

He has since gone on to tease more tracks, collaborating with fellow South Florida rappers such as ohtrapstar, Kid Buu, and producer Jimmy Duval to create the first song he made after moving to L.A., “Legend.”

Icy’s debut album, WINTER CAN BE MURDER, released on September 27, 2019.

songs.title: LINK

description.plain:
Following many teased tracks, but only being his second release of 2018, Icy Narco follows up the dark and gritty track, and his biggest song to date, “#RONNYJIKILLEDTHIS”.

After being previewed on multiple occasions on his Instagram account, the track was officially released on June 14, 2018 being his first release while being signed to a label.

songs.title: Numb & Frozen

description.plain:
Sitting as his third single of 2018 following “LINK” & “#RONNYJIKILLEDTHIS”, on “Numb & Frozen”, Icy Narco takes a more melodic approach telling about his past and his inner-demons.

First being previewed in early 2018 but again in July, “Numb & Frozen” was officially announced as an official release on Icy Narco’s No Jumper Interview in addition to his previously released single “LINK”, and his upcoming track titled “Hypocrites” all expected to appear on his debut project Frozen Fable.
